# Scripts Cursor Rules
# Rules for automation and build scripts

## Script Development
- Make scripts idempotent when possible
- Add proper error handling and exit codes
- Include usage instructions in comments
- Use set -euo pipefail for bash scripts

## Documentation
- Add header comments explaining purpose
- Document required parameters and environment variables
- Include examples of script usage
- Mention any prerequisites or dependencies

## Portability
- Use portable shell commands when possible
- Handle different operating systems appropriately
- Use absolute paths or properly handle relative paths
- Test scripts in different environments

## Maintenance
- Keep scripts simple and focused
- Use version control for all scripts
- Add logging for debugging purposes
- Regular review and cleanup of unused scripts